Added EPA/Play from All QB Rushes

Bar is Rushing EPA/play
Logo is Overall EPA/play

Highest Added EPA/Play from rushes:
1) Fields: +0.13
2) Hurts: +0.11
3) Lamar +0.09
4) Allen +0.08
5) Jones +0.07

#nflverse https://t.co/OH73lEvm2s

Pass Rate Over Expected (PROE)
Weeks 1-17

• 6/9 positive PROE teams have clinched a playoff berth, all 9 could make it
• Bottom 6/7 PROE teams eliminated from playoffs
• Top 4 PROE teams in AFC

NYG: 24th, -4.9%

#nflverse https://t.co/z5MseA9GpX

Cumulative Pass Rate over Expected

Initial darkness shows current ranking

Biggest increase week 4 → week 17
1) 49ers: +6.4% (31st → 21st)
2) Bears: +3.5% (32nd → 32nd)
3) Patriots: +3.3% (27th → 13th)

Biggest increase from week 10:
1) NYG: +2.3% (29th → 24th)

#nflverse https://t.co/ieZasLgZni

NFL Cornerback Receiving Yards allowed per Target vs. Forced Incompletion Rate (data from @PFF):

- Sauce Gardner is ridiculous, DROY without a doubt
- Ravens secondary has struggled
- Darious Williams was an underrated offseason signing by the Jags

#nflverse https://t.co/Ahqs5jspfq

Day 75: Used a #SQL query to get the biggest blowouts by season from 1999-2022, data courtesy of #nflverse

Unsurprisingly, home teams are responsible for the biggest blowouts

The largest one in the last 23 yrs was in 2009 when the Pats beat the Titans 59-0

#100DaysOfCode https://t.co/8dkFWj8xDN

2022_17_BUF_CIN has been deleted from the #nflverse games/schedule listing.

It no longer appears on https://t.co/oFRVeOEB5E

It will not count for the NFL Game Data Prediction Game.

Obviously the AFC matchups are now known:

(7) MIA @ (2) BUF
(6) BAL @ (3) CIN
(5) LAC @ (4) JAX

(1) KC (bye)

I'm not going to put the games on https://t.co/cLipOV1bnf or in the #nflverse games data until we have all the games and know the scheduled dates/times.

Pillboxes!! KC offense vs Denver. The 2PT try was the failed PAT. Jet narrowly edged out Pacheco for most RB snaps. Pacheco only had 1 third down snap. MVS led WR's snaps. JuJu I think was sacrificed to Surtain this week. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/3tGravUF5x

Defense. Sneed went out for a drive in the 4th, replaced by Williams. Drive ended in TD. Gay *mostly* lost the 3rd drive to Harris, as usual. For being run stuffers, Williams and Nnadi were in for a lot of pass plays. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/Zt7rzbARKC

Here's Denvers charts. They too had an OL who went out. Chiefs FA acquisition in 2024 Jerry Jeudy (I'm manifesting this) had a nice game again. Lamar Jackson's name came up a lot in this game, probably because Surtain was ignored. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/omkioeYQgL

The first 18 picks in the draft are now set.

Here is how the draft order would have changed if each team would have flipped their Week 18 result.

Simulation: @nflseedR #nflverse https://t.co/xTrlfYMtRh

According to @ben_bot_baldwin,
Houston Texans had a 0,6% chance of converting 4&12 (20%), 4&20 (7%) and 2PAT (43%) all in this game!

#nflverse https://t.co/aorBaneboB
